    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a univariate time series with 12 monthly observations. Categorical x-axis labels use month abbreviations while quantitative y-values represent sales figures in thousands. Synthetic data was generated with \u03bc=130.2k, \u03c3=44.8k, showing a positive annual trend (+82.4k to +209.7k) with Q2-Q3 seasonality and Q4 decline, maintaining domain-appropriate ranges for retail sales. The spline chart was selected to emphasize trend continuity while smoothing short-term fluctuations, optimizing data-ink ratio by removing excessive gridlines and using minimal contrasting colors. Perceptual effectiveness is achieved through position encoding (month alignment) and length encoding (sales values), with direct labeling eliminating legend dependencies. The synthetic dataset exhibits both linear trend (R\u00b2=0.78) and quarterly cyclical patterns (Q2-Q3 amplitude +37.5% vs baseline), validated through residual analysis."
